post_text: When the Sociology field trip was canceled in March, LTHS students were asked if they wanted the lunch money they’d paid returned or if they wanted to donate it to a good cause. 100% of the students agreed to donate the money. Mrs. Edwards & her class donated the money to a local foster care facility. Mrs. Doornkaat's Sociology classes donated their money to cater a meal, from a local restaurant, for the ICU nurses & doctors at Silver Cross Hospital. #PorterPride
